To cause to make a rattling noise.
To chatter noisily or rapidly.
To hit; to smack.
To eat away bit by bit; to wear away or diminish by gradually separating or destroying small particles of, as by action of a strong acid or a caustic alkali.
To consume; to wear away; to prey upon; to impair.
definitions.example: My morale is being corroded day by day.

definitions.definition: To have corrosive action; to be subject to corrosion.
Damaged by corrosion.
A postdoctoral academic research position.
Someone in such a position.
Without fault; free from defect or error.
